Concerned community members said a child was being locked up alone in a house by her mother. BELA BELA - A disabled girl (12) was found tied to a chair in a locked room by police. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said concerned community members tipped the police off. They said a child was being locked up alone in a house by her mother. Police found the girl and arrested her 30-year-old mother. The woman will appear before the Bela Bela magistrate's court on a charge of child neglect.